  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n- [ ] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\nforge 0.1.0 (77882ab 2022-03-22T00:21:29.105530+00:00)\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\nforge test\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nmacOS (M1)\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nIn test.sh at line [23](https://github.com/maple-labs/contract-test-suite/blob/960ebfc4603a96bb4baee141cba1eb253d0a3dbe/test.sh#L23), DAPP_TEST_ADDRESS is used. This is in a refactor from dapptools to foundry where the contract test address itself needs to be a certain address to interact with permissioned mainnet contracts.\r\n\r\nIt can be seen on lines \r\n[100](https://github.com/maple-labs/contract-test-suite/blob/fc02bfbadb979dd3af987da6c8114658cfee7f32/contracts/test/ClaimTest.t.sol#L100) and [101](https://github.com/maple-labs/contract-test-suite/blob/fc02bfbadb979dd3af987da6c8114658cfee7f32/contracts/test/ClaimTest.t.sol#L101) that `msg.sender` and `address(this)` are logged, and produce the following output:\r\n\r\n```\r\n    ├─ emit log_named_address(key: \"msg.sender         \", val: 0xa6ccb9483e3e7a737e3a4f5b72a1ce51838ba122)\r\n    ├─ emit log_named_address(key: \"address(this)      \", val: 0xb8df2f8992e3855c99db39a7fce7aaeacb347c49)\r\n```\r\n\r\n`0xa6ccb9483e3e7a737e3a4f5b72a1ce51838ba122` is the desired value for `address(this)`.\r\n\r\nI believe it is because of this line here: https://github.com/gakonst/foundry/blob/0cde8701496dff9f28c9025fc8c8721ba55ece7c/config/src/lib.rs#L1040\r\n\r\n",
